Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.35,0:00:06.73,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Then that woman who hired you to investigate\Nwhether or not her boyfriend was cheating...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.44,0:00:09.44,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.19,0:00:11.95,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,She fell down a stone staircase.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.99,0:00:15.41,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}Tsuge! How dare you come here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.24,0:00:15.41,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kaoru Sasamori (24)\NDeceased
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.45,0:00:17.49,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.49,0:00:18.12,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't play dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.41,0:00:22.87,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Takashi Sasamori (28)\NKaoru's Elder Brother / Photographer
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.91,0:00:21.62,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}You were just using her{blu: toying with her}, weren't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.62,0:00:26.88,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}Then when your marriage drew near, Kaoru became\Na nuisance, so you pushed her down a stone staircase!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.21,0:00:28.80,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hikari Tsuge (33)\NKaoru's Ex-boyfriend / Sculptor
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.67,0:00:28.80,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}Talk about nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.59,0:00:30.92,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I saw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.92,0:00:34.22,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You were at the top of the staircase Kaoru fell from!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.22,0:00:35.93,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}P-Please, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.93,0:00:40.27,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mariko Noguchi (30)\NTsuge's Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.34,0:00:40.27,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}The police investigation already determined that to be a simple misunderstanding!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.77,0:00:41.85,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.85,0:00:44.10,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You might have fooled the police, but not me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.10,0:00:44.77,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.40,0:00:47.77,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You two, please cut it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.11,0:00:53.28,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kazumi Ishikura (25)\NKaoru's friend / Ballerina
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.31,0:00:51.57,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}Don't argue in front of Kaoru.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.57,0:00:53.28,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}Please let her rest in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.20,0:00:58.12,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She's right. Remember, this is a funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.03,0:01:04.29,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No matter how much you might hate me, I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.29,0:01:05.25,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If you excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.87,0:01:07.50,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hey, Tsuge{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.33,0:01:09.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was three months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.55,0:01:17.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then this morning, Tsuge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} contacted\Nyou and said he'd reveal who killed her?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.68,0:01:18.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.47,0:01:24.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It doesn't matter how many times you try,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.48,0:01:26.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}whether it's in love, cases, today, or tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.35,0:01:29.77,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What is the real meaning behind an artist's unusual piece of art?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.77,0:01:31.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.78,0:01:33.53,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.53,0:01:36.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.00,0:03:30.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.62,0:03:36.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, there was a landslide up ahead, so this road's blocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.34,0:03:38.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.01,0:03:41.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were trying to get to that house.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.43,0:03:42.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.55,0:03:46.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's on that road, so you should be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.56,0:03:47.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.19,0:03:53.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, I can barely see what's in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.02,0:03:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you drive all right? Be careful, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.82,0:03:59.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, who else is coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.15,0:04:04.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he called the three who'd\Nbeen arguing at the funeral, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.00,0:04:14.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like someone else got here first.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.93,0:04:26.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, did Tsuge call you here too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.43,0:04:27.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.85,0:04:35.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's raining cats and dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.44,0:04:36.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, let's go in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.99,0:04:43.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umm, whose car is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.16,0:04:45.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's Tsuge's.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.53,0:04:49.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These past three months he's secluded himself in this atelier while working on a piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.58,0:04:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no, he forgot to lock the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.83,0:04:57.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsuge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! It's me, Noguchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.42,0:05:02.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.05,0:05:05.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I forgot to bring an umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.72,0:05:07.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.97,0:05:08.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.43,0:05:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, you should hurry and dry off your clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.57,0:05:23.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsuge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.58,0:05:29.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.12,0:05:30.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, call the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.33,0:05:32.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.41,0:05:35.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The crime scene must be preserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.08,0:05:36.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everybody, please leave the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.96,0:05:38.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.25,0:05:43.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please make sure they don't touch that piece of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.51,0:05:45.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? That's art?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.05,0:05:48.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like a pile of junk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.05,0:05:50.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there really any point in something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.97,0:05:52.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-How rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.85,0:05:55.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you making fun of Tsuge's work?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.10,0:05:56.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.52,0:06:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'll make sure to tell the police, so could you leave the room for now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.11,0:06:05.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you will? I'm trusting you here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.70,0:06:07.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I've got it, understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.87,0:06:10.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.41,0:06:16.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's no dust on top of the tape,\Nso there was something there recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.46,0:06:18.88,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is that a screen?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.17,0:06:23.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"Demurrer"...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.59,0:06:26.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If I recall correctly, that means something like "a declaration of objection".
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.63,0:06:27.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.64,0:06:30.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't go wandering about!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.01,0:06:32.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.14,0:06:38.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just what was there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.81,0:06:42.52,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And who moved it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.28,0:06:52.16,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's nothing anywhere in the house that'd look like it'd fit, so the killer probably took it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.33,0:06:55.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim is Hikari Tsuge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.29,0:06:58.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Real name, Ritsu Hikage, 33 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.75,0:07:00.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He worked as a sculptor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.83,0:07:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, it seems "Hikari Tsuge" was an anagram of his real name, "Ritsu Hikage".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.30,0:07:11.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An "anagram" is when you rearrange the order of letters in a word to create another one, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.64,0:07:12.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.72,0:07:16.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cause of death was intercranial injury from a blow to the back of the head. {mb "blunt-force trauma to the head"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.18,0:07:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A hammer that we believe to be the weapon was found lying nearby, but any possible fingerprints had been wiped off it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.07,0:07:27.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, just to confirm...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.19,0:07:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone here was invited by the victim, who was to reveal who was behind a previous incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.41,0:07:35.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.33,0:07:40.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the time we arrived, he was no longer\Nbreathing and the killer had already escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.96,0:07:43.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.29,0:07:50.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to the police officer at the checkpoint, absolutely nobody came down from the road that leads to this atelier.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.59,0:07:53.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, that means whoever did it is still around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.43,0:07:55.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We must consider that possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.97,0:08:02.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, to begin with, there were only four cars that\Ncame this way instead of turning around, he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.90,0:08:04.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only four cars, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.11,0:08:08.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So me, Kazumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Sasamori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nand Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and company.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.15,0:08:10.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the killer's right here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.07,0:08:18.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see. There's only one direct road leading here,\Nand there's a checkpoint right before it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.87,0:08:24.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Escaping down the slope in this rain and total darkness would be impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.21,0:08:26.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Which means this area's truly a closed circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.96,0:08:29.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.59,0:08:36.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, we were the first ones to arrive and everyone else followed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.14,0:08:38.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. I was the first one who arrived after you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.47,0:08:42.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came behind him, and Noguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got here last.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.85,0:08:47.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, we entered the atelier\Ntogether and discovered the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.82,0:08:48.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.98,0:08:49.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.94,0:08:57.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we told him we were coming to this\Natelier, the officer said "you too", didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.66,0:09:02.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means there was another car that came to the atelier before us, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.58,0:09:08.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'd be able to find out the killer if we ask that officer about that car's model or driver, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.71,0:09:12.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, although he remembered there were four cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.22,0:09:16.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he said he couldn't remember any of the drivers' faces nor their cars' models.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.76,0:09:19.85,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's no way I could tell with all this rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.39,0:09:22.06,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Come on, I was counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.06,0:09:25.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, to summarize all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.36,0:09:32.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To begin with, there was a single car at the atelier, which belonged to the deceased Tsuge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.03,0:09:35.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and company arrived here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.66,0:09:38.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was followed by three more cars, making it a group of four.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.33,0:09:43.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, according to what the officer said, another car passed him before Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.83,0:09:45.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.13,0:09:54.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first car to arrive was the killer's, who killed Tsuge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, then left the atelier and hid somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.76,0:09:59.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, when everybody showed up, joined them as if nothing had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.56,0:10:00.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what must've happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.31,0:10:03.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, what was the motive of the crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.52,0:10:05.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To silence him, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.60,0:10:13.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hearing that Tsuge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would reveal who had killed Kaoru Sasamori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} three months ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.11,0:10:16.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer rushed to the atelier as soon as they could and murdered him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.99,0:10:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the person behind this\Nmurder is also Kaoru Sasamori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.58,0:10:24.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that person is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.29,0:10:32.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of you three!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.59,0:10:35.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.80,0:10:39.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Thank you, Captain Obvious.{Given the situation, that much was obvious.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.64,0:10:45.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The problem is {\i1}which{\i0} of the three did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.73,0:10:56.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on a sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.52,0:11:03.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we assume the killer's among us three, and Tsuge\Nknew it, then why would he call that person?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.62,0:11:07.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he was trying to play detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.70,0:11:11.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He did act childish at times.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.00,0:11:19.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so does that mean he summoned us all the way to this\Natelier because he wanted to proclaim the killer was one of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.55,0:11:20.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.97,0:11:23.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'm not the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.76,0:11:27.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That day, I'd promised to have dinner with my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.68,0:11:32.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I got pushed into holding a photo shoot,\Nso I was a little late, and when I went to meet her...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.98,0:11:39.15,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Kaoru?! Are you okay, Kaoru?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.90,0:11:42.95,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Somebody... from behind me...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.95,0:11:44.91,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Someone pushed you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.70,0:11:47.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure I saw him back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.78,0:11:51.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I caught a glimpse of Tsuge atop the stone staircase.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.08,0:11:55.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I was convinced Tsuge was the one behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.38,0:11:58.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it wasn't like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.50,0:12:01.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsuge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was a witness, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.59,0:12:04.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I can't be the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.30,0:12:08.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, there's nobody who could prove that, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.10,0:12:11.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you calling me a liar?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.64,0:12:12.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kaoru was my sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.93,0:12:16.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you didn't get along all that well, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.06,0:12:22.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She told me that you were disputing how your parents' inheritance would be split with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.32,0:12:24.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She told you that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.20,0:12:25.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you got fed up...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.82,0:12:29.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and pushed Kaoru down the staircase, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.37,0:12:30.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'd you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.83,0:12:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please hold on, Kazumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.41,0:12:36.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You might look like you were really close friends with her...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.25,0:12:39.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But didn't you have a motive for killing Kaoru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.63,0:12:43.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.17,0:12:46.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see, Tsuge was with another woman besides Kaoru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.72,0:12:47.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.43,0:12:53.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was hired to find exactly who.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.27,0:12:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.64,0:12:59.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, that other woman you mentioned...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.44,0:13:01.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was Kazumi Ishikura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.86,0:13:08.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't know he was going out with Kaoru either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.08,0:13:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.16,0:13:16.16,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Tsuge{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10} just proposed to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.16,0:13:17.16,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.16,0:13:18.67,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What the hell is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.63,0:13:25.17,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10null.AR: It looks like Tsuge is saying somebody's name before being cut off by Kazumi}Tsuge{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10}, what does this mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.17,0:13:28.18,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm talking about work right now. Wait until I'm done.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.68,0:13:30.89,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How long have you been dating Kaoru?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.89,0:13:31.93,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It isn't like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.93,0:13:33.93,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't play dumb with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.93,0:13:37.56,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Break up! Break up with her!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.81,0:13:41.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even so, it's not like you didn't have a motive to kill her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.73,0:13:45.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sister once told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.57,0:13:47.28,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Kaoru{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10}, take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.90,0:13:49.49,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.49,0:13:51.49,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's one million yen inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.49,0:13:53.99,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I want you to split up with Tsuge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.99,0:13:55.20,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.20,0:13:57.29,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ever since you two started dating,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.29,0:13:59.33,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Tsuge's barely worked at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.33,0:14:01.13,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So, take this and split up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.13,0:14:02.46,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.17,0:14:10.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard that since Tsuge was barely working,\Nyour clients started looking for different artists.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.93,0:14:14.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that happened, you'd have to pay a huge amount of money for breach of contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.51,0:14:17.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying I killed Kaoru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} over that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.89,0:14:23.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that ever since Kaoru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died, Tsuge started devoting himself to his work like he was possessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.48,0:14:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that had nothing to do with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.49,0:14:34.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Inspector Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.62,0:14:36.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.58,0:14:39.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle Kogorō wanted me to ask you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.12,0:14:44.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to check if there's any possible hiding places for\Na car between the police checkpoint and here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.79,0:14:45.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.84,0:14:56.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.47,0:14:59.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll just take a quick look!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.60,0:15:00.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.02,0:15:06.69,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Over here, that cabin'd be in the way, so you wouldn't be seen by cars coming up the hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.69,0:15:07.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.32,0:15:09.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is this it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.69,0:15:13.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The object that was taken from the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.57,0:15:16.53,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In which case, it's just like I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.33,0:15:19.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.33,0:15:26.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like all of you to accompany me to the\Nstation so we can hear your stories one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.55,0:15:30.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.34,0:15:32.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's time for Sleeping Kogorō!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.88,0:15:35.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no need to go to the police station.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.01,0:15:38.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, I'll settle this here and now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.06,0:15:38.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.52,0:15:46.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I found Tsuge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body here in the atelier,\NI spotted traces of an object having been taken away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.73,0:15:47.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An object?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.90,0:15:53.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Taking the situation into account, the perpetrator\Nmost likely took it away after the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.82,0:15:55.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi, bring it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.36,0:15:56.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.24,0:16:05.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did Tsuge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} let three months pass before\Nstating he'd reveal Kaoru Sasamori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.88,0:16:12.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could've revealed the killer on the day of Kaoru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nfuneral, when he got into an argument with Sasamori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.92,0:16:13.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.97,0:16:24.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsuge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} probably wanted to identify the killer in his own way, and three months were necessary to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.06,0:16:25.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You couldn't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.69,0:16:30.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Correct. The time he took producing the objet d'art you see before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.44,0:16:33.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This piece of art is titled "Demurrer".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.74,0:16:36.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means "a declaration of objection".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.03,0:16:37.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I've brought it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.99,0:16:43.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you please, place it at the back of the\Nroom, aligned with the sellotape marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.08,0:16:44.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.83,0:16:51.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember this. His artistic name, Hikari Tsuge,\Nwas an anagram of his real name, Ritsu Hikage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.96,0:16:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Hikari Tsuge" and "Ritsu Hikage"...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.09,0:16:55.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}hikari
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.09,0:16:55.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}hikage
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.09,0:16:55.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Truly an artist of light and shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.38,0:17:00.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if you take the title of this piece of art, "Demurrer", to be an anagram...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.56,0:17:04.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the original title, a new one emerges...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.56,0:17:06.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Murderer".
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.81,0:17:09.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An alternate title, hidden in the shadow.{literal translation: "Murderer" - a shadow title.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.36,0:17:13.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It has an alternate title of "murderer"?{literal translation: "Murderer" - a shadow title, huh?}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.82,0:17:15.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The preparations are done.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.82,0:17:22.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, lower the projector screen that's above the door and turn off the room lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.33,0:17:22.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.83,0:17:28.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi, turn on the lamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.46,0:17:29.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood. {null.AR: Kogoro's speech pattern is a bit assertive, so it could be either "turn the reflector on" or simply "the reflector"}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.92,0:17:34.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about this is related to a murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.76,0:17:39.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi, turn the sculpture's base around slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.59,0:17:41.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.64,0:17:46.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.65,0:17:51.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shadow art.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.06,0:17:53.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's impossible to tell what the piece is on a first glance,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.57,0:17:58.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but when light shines on it from a certain\Nangle, an artistic shadow emerges.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.95,0:18:04.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsuge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was trying to identify the killer through his work.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.54,0:18:07.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, turn the lights back on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.87,0:18:10.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazumi Ishikura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.87,0:18:15.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the one behind the deaths of Kaoru Sasamori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Hikari Tsuge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! {null.AR: I'm affirming, but Kogoro's sort of asking ("desu ne")}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.38,0:18:19.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on a second, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.22,0:18:23.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a bit of a stretch to identify her as the\Nmurderer just with a shadow of a ballerina.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.68,0:18:27.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you say, that shadow alone isn't strong enough evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.93,0:18:33.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the lamp was removed from the scene\Nout of fear that the shadow would be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.15,0:18:38.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that action itself is irrefutable\Nevidence pointing towards the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.53,0:18:40.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{RED: workbench, GREEN: tool rack}Think back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.82,0:18:45.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To reach the lamp's position you would have to step over Tsuge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.91,0:18:48.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, there was a pool of blood on the other side,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.54,0:18:53.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so the killer couldn't step over it,\Nas footprints would be left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.08,0:18:57.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, just like Conan did\Nback when we discovered the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.84,0:19:02.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer crawled underneath the workbench\Nto fetch the lamp from the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.59,0:19:10.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry if I sound rude, but Sasamori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Noguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s physiques\Nprevent them from crawling underneath the workbench.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.85,0:19:16.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only one who could've passed through there was the ballerina, Ishikura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.65,0:19:19.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's one last thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.65,0:19:24.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you got out of your car, you didn't have an umbrella, and were soaking wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.49,0:19:31.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Conan told me that the driver's seat in your car was also drenched.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.04,0:19:35.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, you were already drenched before leaving your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.54,0:19:39.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because you went out in the rain in order to throw away the lamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.13,0:19:46.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were supposed to get married.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.43,0:19:48.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At least, that's what I believed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.43,0:19:57.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So when I heard he called all of you here, I thought he intended to announce our engagement, so I rushed here straight away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.57,0:20:04.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But instead, Tsuge showed me the shadow art and identified me as a murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.91,0:20:08.95,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What are you talking about? Weren't we\Ngoing to announce our engagement today?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.45,0:20:13.37,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You told me you'd marry me if Kaoru was gone, didn't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.37,0:20:19.92,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That woman was getting so annoying, she even hired\Na detective to sniff about, so I just said that out of frustration.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.38,0:20:22.13,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I never thought you'd take me seriously
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.13,0:20:24.72,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and actually go kill her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.72,0:20:26.84,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She was your best friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.64,0:20:36.35,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Kaoru?! Are you okay, Kaoru?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.02,0:20:39.23,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Talk about betraying a friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.86,0:20:44.57,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I won't say anything bad if you surrender youself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.36,0:20:49.07,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I called a detective named Kogorō Mouri here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.66,0:20:52.79,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That guy should be able to take you to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.79,0:20:55.00,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If you want, I can introduce you to a good lawyer—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.68,0:21:16.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.31,0:21:19.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why didn't you break the sculpture?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.86,0:21:22.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way, you wouldn't have had to conceal the lamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.74,0:21:26.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was more than that she {\i1}didn't{\i0} break it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.90,0:21:28.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She {\i1}couldn't{\i0} break it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.45,0:21:31.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I couldn't break it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.16,0:21:35.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.83,0:21:39.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As even if he made it just to accuse me,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.71,0:21:45.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it meant that he was thinking about me for the\Nwhole three months he worked on this piece of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.55,0:21:48.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, I couldn't break it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.47,0:23:18.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.76,0:23:20.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're drinking too much beer!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.68,0:23:23.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, why are the lights off?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.81,0:23:27.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shut up! Just you watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.02,0:23:30.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is my shadow art, y'see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.99,0:23:33.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.07,0:23:38.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing, it's Mom's profile!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.33,0:23:39.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-S-S-So it seems...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.83,0:23:43.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess you do have artistic talent, right, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.83,0:23:45.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I... I guess so...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.63,0:23:49.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From now on, call me "Art Kogorō"!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.47,0:23:55.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,More like "Argh" Kogorō Mouri, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.26,0:23:57.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.26,0:24:02.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran and two of her friends discover\Nan odd corpse on the way to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.85,0:24:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And next to it, there is...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.31,0:24:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan: Yūsaku Kudō's Cold Case (Part I)!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.35,0:24:14.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Candy!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.27,0:24:15.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}tō{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.27,0:24:15.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad's cold case, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.86,0:24:16.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who do you mean by "dad"?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.82,0:24:19.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I meant Saitō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Saitō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! { いや さいとうさんだろ さいとさん！ null.AR: Could be "さいとさん" as well}
